Description: Glazed composition lentoid flask; mould-made; neck tapering to everted rim with round mouth; two modelled vertical strap handles from below rim to shoulder; body lentoid; traces of blueish green glaze preserved.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Turner Bequest Excavations, Enkomi
Bibliographic references: Murray, Smith and Walters 1900 / Excavations in Cyprus (P40, Fig 68)
Jacobsson 1994 / Aegyptiaca from Late Bronze Age Cyprus (No. 168)
